the tables have turned.

259
00:14:51,024 --> 00:14:52,225
Tsezguerra: You really think so?

260
00:14:52,259 --> 00:14:53,460
Men: Eh?

261
00:14:53,493 --> 00:14:54,594
Tsezguerra:
From where i’m sitting,

262
00:14:54,628 --> 00:14:57,097
our team is the one
on the ropes.

263
00:14:57,130 --> 00:15:00,000
Hisoka probably isn’t
in any shape to throw.

264
00:15:00,033 --> 00:15:02,269
I’d be surprised
if he could even

265
00:15:02,302 --> 00:15:04,905
hold the ball
with his right hand.

266
00:15:04,938 --> 00:15:07,441
Gon’s attacks used
a huge amount of aura.

267
00:15:07,474 --> 00:15:09,209
That takes its toll.

268
00:15:09,243 --> 00:15:11,979
He should feel completely
drained right about now.

269
00:15:12,012 --> 00:15:13,914
( Gon grunts )

270
00:15:13,947 --> 00:15:17,384
Tsezguerra: Can he muster
another attack that powerful?

271
00:15:17,417 --> 00:15:19,419
It’s highly unlikely.

272
00:15:19,453 --> 00:15:23,290
Barry: That means killua’s
the only uninjured one inside?

273
00:15:23,323 --> 00:15:24,524
Tsezguerra: Quite the opposite.

274
00:15:24,558 --> 00:15:26,026
( Men gasp )

275
00:15:26,059 --> 00:15:28,562
Tsezguerra: I would venture
that of the three,

276
00:15:28,595 --> 00:15:31,364
he’s probably
the most gravely injured.

277
00:15:31,398 --> 00:15:33,533
Rodriot: What do you mean?

278
00:15:33,567 --> 00:15:36,470
( Gon exhales )

279
00:15:36,503 --> 00:15:38,872
Killua: Are you
doin’ okay there, gon?

280
00:15:38,906 --> 00:15:42,877
Gon: Yeah, but I think
the next one will be the last,

281
00:15:42,910 --> 00:15:44,512
so i’ll give it
everything i’ve got.

282
00:15:44,545 --> 00:15:47,548
Killua: All right.
Just make it good.

283
00:15:49,049 --> 00:15:51,518
One more. I can take it.

284
00:15:51,552 --> 00:15:54,889
I’ve just gotta hold out.

285
00:15:54,922 --> 00:15:57,892
Tsezguerra: When gon struck
the ball, I noticed that killua

286
00:15:57,925 --> 00:16:02,062
barely used any protective nen
on his hands.

287
00:16:02,095 --> 00:16:04,898
Kess: That’s crazy.
That launch was intense.

288
00:16:04,932 --> 00:16:06,901
He was like a damn Cannon.

289
00:16:06,934 --> 00:16:08,135
Tsezguerra: Correct,

290
00:16:08,168 --> 00:16:11,505
and essentially
killua used his bare hands

291
00:16:11,538 --> 00:16:13,673
to form that cannon’s barrel.

292
00:16:13,707 --> 00:16:16,143
But with
the right amount of nen,

293
00:16:16,176 --> 00:16:18,979
if he’d used
just enough to protect them,

294
00:16:19,012 --> 00:16:23,049
his aura would have become
a barrier against gon’s punch,

295
00:16:23,083 --> 00:16:26,320
significantly reducing
the amount of power to the ball.

296
00:16:26,353 --> 00:16:30,023
In order to keep himself from
weakening the ball’s velocity,

297
00:16:30,057 --> 00:16:33,060
killua used hardly
any aura on his hands,

298
00:16:33,093 --> 00:16:35,395
sacrificing them
in the process.

299
00:16:35,429 --> 00:16:38,198
That tells me that as bad
as hisoka’s right hand

300
00:16:38,232 --> 00:16:39,934
might be at the moment,

301
00:16:39,967 --> 00:16:43,070
killua’s hands must be
in much worse condition.

302
00:16:43,103 --> 00:16:45,539
Damn.
I feel like such a fool.

303
00:16:45,572 --> 00:16:48,275
Why am I not
up there with them?

304
00:16:48,308 --> 00:16:53,313
I know the technique, and I can
do it much faster than killua.

305
00:16:53,347 --> 00:16:56,050
In the moment
before gon touches the ball,

306
00:16:56,083 --> 00:16:58,686
I could swiftly switch
my aura to my hands,

307
00:16:58,719 --> 00:17:01,121
a near-instant transfer.

308
00:17:02,122 --> 00:17:03,290
Wait.

309
00:17:03,323 --> 00:17:06,493
Timeout. Hey, ref, question.

310
00:17:06,527 --> 00:17:08,062
Number zero: Yes, what is it?

311
00:17:08,095 --> 00:17:09,430
Tsezguerra: I was just wondering

312
00:17:09,463 --> 00:17:11,098
if the players
inside of the court

313
00:17:11,131 --> 00:17:13,400
can choose to move
to the outside.

314
00:17:13,433 --> 00:17:16,136
Number zero: Well,
that doesn’t violate any rules,

315
00:17:16,170 --> 00:17:18,673
but be aware
that you can’t return inside.

316
00:17:18,705 --> 00:17:21,074
Tsezguerra: All right.
Come here!

317
00:17:22,643 --> 00:17:25,746
Gon, if you just step outside
of the court before you strike,

318
00:17:25,779 --> 00:17:27,414
I can hold the ball for you.

319
00:17:27,447 --> 00:17:30,650
Killua’s hands must be
totally ravaged by now.

320
00:17:30,684 --> 00:17:33,153
I sincerely doubt
that he’s in any condition

321
00:17:33,187 --> 00:17:35,222
to hold the ball
or anything else.

322
00:17:35,255 --> 00:17:37,224
♪

323
00:17:37,257 --> 00:17:41,194
I know a way that’ll allow me
to protect my hands

324
00:17:41,228 --> 00:17:43,664
with a lightning-fast
coating of aura.

325
00:17:43,697 --> 00:17:47,668
I can hold the ball while you
take out razor from here.

326
00:17:47,701 --> 00:17:50,537
It’s the only way
that we can win this.

327
00:17:50,571 --> 00:17:52,740
Killua: We can’t do that.

328
00:17:52,773 --> 00:17:56,143
Tsezguerra: But why not?
What’s the problem with that?

329
00:17:56,176 --> 00:17:58,011
Killua: It feels like a cop-out.

330
00:17:58,045 --> 00:17:59,313
Tsezguerra: You’re kidding!

331
00:17:59,346 --> 00:18:01,548
This is not the time
to be thinking like that!

332
00:18:01,582 --> 00:18:03,617
( Groans, coughs )

333
00:18:03,650 --> 00:18:05,585
Killua: Hey,
don’t overdo it, old man.

334
00:18:05,619 --> 00:18:07,087
You took a hit.

335
00:18:07,120 --> 00:18:08,688
You’re only gonna
make it feel worse.

336
00:18:08,722 --> 00:18:10,290
I’m doin’ fine.

337
00:18:10,324 --> 00:18:12,459
I’m not hurt nearly as bad
as you might think.

338
00:18:12,492 --> 00:18:15,128
Tsezguerra: Okay, then.
Show me your hands.

339
00:18:15,162 --> 00:18:17,064
Killua: I said i’m fine.

340
00:18:17,097 --> 00:18:18,265
( Killua winces )

341
00:18:23,704 --> 00:18:24,672
( Tsezguerra gasps )

342
00:18:24,705 --> 00:18:27,474
♪

343
00:18:30,110 --> 00:18:31,478
Like I thought.

344
00:18:31,512 --> 00:18:34,448
I’ll bet you he can’t feel
anything but pain.

345
00:18:34,481 --> 00:18:35,682
Killua: I can do this!

346
00:18:35,716 --> 00:18:38,352
I can take one more, okay?

347
00:18:38,385 --> 00:18:40,387
Gon, I know I can do it.

348
00:18:40,420 --> 00:18:42,589
Tsezguerra: Impossible.
I’m right.

349
00:18:42,623 --> 00:18:44,425
Please help me convince him.

350
00:18:46,159 --> 00:18:48,795
Gon: I--i already knew...

351
00:18:48,829 --> 00:18:52,166
That killua’s hands were hurt.

352
00:18:53,233 --> 00:18:54,735
I’m sorry, Mr. Tsezguerra,

353
00:18:54,768 --> 00:18:57,404
but I won’t move
out of the court.

354
00:18:57,437 --> 00:18:58,605
Tsezguerra: Eh?

355
00:18:58,639 --> 00:19:02,409
Gon: I need him
to hold the ball for me.

356
00:19:02,442 --> 00:19:05,211
I can’t do this without killua.

357
00:19:05,245 --> 00:19:08,215
( Killua gasps )

358
00:19:08,248 --> 00:19:10,717
Gon: If biscuit
or hisoka held it,

359
00:19:10,751 --> 00:19:13,354
I probably couldn’t use
my full strength.

360
00:19:13,387 --> 00:19:14,822
There’s only one reason

361
00:19:14,855 --> 00:19:17,725
I can focus everything i’ve got
on hitting the ball.

362
00:19:17,758 --> 00:19:21,428
It’s because I know
killua’s the one holding it.

363
00:19:28,268 --> 00:19:31,238
Killua: There it is, old man.
Do you get it now?

364
00:19:31,271 --> 00:19:33,406
Why don’t you go get some rest?

365
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:35,175
Tsezguerra: I understand.

366
00:19:35,209 --> 00:19:36,544
Good luck.

367
00:19:36,577 --> 00:19:38,879
♪

368
00:19:38,912 --> 00:19:41,615
Bisky: The ball,
give it here, hisoka.

369
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:44,384
Number zero: We will
now resume the match.

370
00:19:47,221 --> 00:19:49,190
Bisky: Now,
to be perfectly honest,

371
00:19:49,223 --> 00:19:51,559
i’m not very good at throwing!

372
00:19:55,696 --> 00:19:57,565
Looks to me like we’re even.

373
00:19:57,598 --> 00:19:59,467
Kess: Brilliant!

374
00:19:59,500 --> 00:20:02,670
The way she hit him
is rebounding the ball to us.

375
00:20:02,703 --> 00:20:03,704
( Groans )

376
00:20:06,907 --> 00:20:09,476
Number zero: Number two is out.

377
00:20:09,510 --> 00:20:11,779
Hisoka: And that means
we’re down to...

378
00:20:14,581 --> 00:20:16,183
Gon: Razor himself.

379
00:20:18,719 --> 00:20:22,690
Killua: Gon, first we need
to get the ball back from razor.

380
00:20:22,723 --> 00:20:24,558
Gon: No sweat.

381
00:20:24,591 --> 00:20:25,692
Oh.

382
00:20:25,726 --> 00:20:26,927
One sec.

383
00:20:29,530 --> 00:20:32,733
Hisoka: I see. Sounds like fun.

384
00:20:32,766 --> 00:20:36,203
Killua: Yeah. I’m just
not convinced it’s gonna work.

385
00:20:36,236 --> 00:20:37,504
Hisoka: Maybe not,

386
00:20:37,538 --> 00:20:40,241
but i’d certainly
love to try either way.

387
00:20:40,274 --> 00:20:42,510
Gon: Let’s give it
a shot, killua.

388
00:20:42,543 --> 00:20:43,811
Killua: Okay.

389
00:20:43,844 --> 00:20:46,313
Hisoka: I believe
that settles it. ( Giggles )

390
00:20:47,781 --> 00:20:49,449
Killua: Man...

391
00:20:49,483 --> 00:20:52,720
You always come up with
the craziest ideas, don’t you?

392
00:20:52,753 --> 00:20:54,221
( Gon laughs )

393
00:20:54,254 --> 00:20:56,223
I’m counting on you.

394
00:20:56,256 --> 00:20:59,326
Number zero: We will
now resume the match!

395
00:20:59,359 --> 00:21:00,827
♪

396
00:21:02,863 --> 00:21:07,334
Narrator: Gon and killua share
a powerful bond of mutual trust.

397
00:21:07,367 --> 00:21:09,269
Their friendship is strong,

398
00:21:09,303 --> 00:21:12,306
but when hisoka
is added to the equation,

399
00:21:12,339 --> 00:21:15,776
there’s no telling what sort
of secret play will emerge.

400
00:21:15,809 --> 00:21:17,811
( Singing in Japanese )

